      <h1 class="h4 mb-3">4. Write to the DOM</h1>
      <div class="tutorial-content mb-4">
        <p>We're already using refs to attach an event listener, but of course you can also write any imperative javascript to work with the DOM.</p>
        <p>This example adds another ref and writes to the element's <code>textContent</code> property. We're not really seeing anything new here, just extending what we've already seen.</p>
        <p>Reference documentation:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="reference/components#het-ref"><code>het-ref</code></a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <form method="post" action="/preview" target="tutorial-preview" data-tutorial-form>
        <input type="hidden" name="html" data-editor-output="html">
        <input type="hidden" name="js" data-editor-output="js">
        <input type="hidden" name="css" data-editor-output="css">

        <div class="mb-3">
          <label class="form-label fw-semibold" for="html-source">HTML</label>
          <textarea id="html-source" class="d-none" data-editor="html">&lt;section het-component="statusButton">
  &lt;button type="button" het-ref="button">Update status&lt;/button>
  &lt;p het-ref="status">Waiting&lt;/p>
&lt;/section></textarea>
          <div class="editor-host" data-editor-host="html"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-3">
          <label class="form-label fw-semibold" for="js-source">JavaScript</label>
          <textarea id="js-source" class="d-none" data-editor="js">HET.registerComponent('statusButton', ({ refs, onCleanup }) => {
  function handleClick() {
    refs.status.textContent = 'Clicked';
  }

  refs.button.addEventListener('click', handleClick);

  onCleanup(() => {
    refs.button.removeEventListener('click', handleClick);
  });
});

HET.init();</textarea>
          <div class="editor-host" data-editor-host="js"></div>
        </div>
        <textarea class="d-none" data-editor="css"></textarea>

        <button class="btn btn-primary" type="submit">Submit</button>
      </form>

      <nav class="d-flex justify-content-between gap-2 mt-4" aria-label="Tutorial section navigation">
          <a class="btn btn-outline-primary" href="/components/cleaning-up-resources">Previous</a>
